msgstr "Eine manuelle Freigabe ist nicht nötig"

msgid "Require administrators to approve new accounts."
msgstr "Administratoren müssen neue Konten genehmigen."
"Neue Benutzer-Konten müssen erst durch einen Administrator freigeschaltet "
"werden."

msgid ""
"Newly registered accounts can either be placed into a manual approval queue "
"for administrative review, or automatically activated immediately. The "
"approval queue is enabled by default because it gives you greater control "
"over who can register an account and access the server.\n"
"\n"
"If your install is completely public, or on a VPN, or users can only "
"register with a trusted provider like LDAP, or you've otherwise configured "
"the server to prevent unauthorized registration, you can disable the queue "
"to reduce administrative overhead.\n"
"\n"
"NOTE: Before you disable the queue, make sure @{config:auth.email-domains} "
"is configured correctly for your install!"
msgstr ""

msgid "Only allow registration from particular domains."
msgstr "Registrierung nur von bestimmten Domains erlauben."

msgid ""
"You can restrict allowed email addresses to certain domains (like "
"`yourcompany.com`) by setting a list of allowed domains here.\n"
"\n"
"Users will only be allowed to register using email addresses at one of the "
"domains, and will only be able to add new email addresses for these domains. "
"If you configure this, it implies @{config:auth.require-email-"
"verification}.\n"
"\n"
"You should omit the `@` from domains. Note that the domain must match "
"exactly. If you allow `yourcompany.com`, that permits `joe@yourcompany.com` "
"but rejects `joe@mail.yourcompany.com`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Valid Setting"
msgstr "Gültiger Wert"

msgid "Auth provider config must be unlocked before editing"
msgstr "Auth-Anbieter-Konfiguration muss vor der Bearbeitung entsperrt werden"

msgid "Auth provider config can be edited without unlocking"
msgstr "Auth-Anbieter-Konfiguration kann ohne Entsperren bearbeitet werden"

msgid ""
"Require administrators to unlock the authentication provider configuration "
"from the CLI before it can be edited."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When set to `true`, the authentication provider configuration for this "
"instance can not be modified without first running `bin/auth unlock` from "
"the command line. This is to reduce the security impact of a compromised "
"administrator account. \n"
"\n"
"After running `bin/auth unlock` and making your changes to the "
"authentication provider config, you should run `bin/auth lock`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Allow editing"
msgstr "Bearbeitung erlauben"

msgid "Prevent editing"
msgstr "Bearbeitung verhindern"

msgid "Determines whether or not basic account information is editable."
msgstr "Bestimmt, ob grundlegende Kontoinformationen bearbeitbar sind."

msgid ""
"This option controls whether users can edit account email addresses and "
"profile real names.\n"
"\n"
"If you set things up to automatically synchronize account information from "
"some other authoritative system, you can prevent users from making these "
"edits to ensure information remains consistent across both systems."
msgstr ""

msgid "Minimum password length."
msgstr "Mindestlänge des Passworts."

msgid ""
"When users set or reset a password, it must have at least this many "
"characters."
msgstr ""

msgid "Cluster Setup"
msgstr "Cluster-Setup"

msgid "Configure services to run on a cluster of hosts."
msgstr "Dienste für den Betrieb auf einem Host-Cluster konfigurieren."

msgid "Cluster: Databases"
msgstr "Cluster: Datenbanken"


#, php-format
msgid ""
"WARNING: This is a prototype option and the description below is currently "
"pure\n"
"fantasy.\n"
"\n"
"This option allows you to make this service aware of database read replicas "
"so\n"
"it can monitor database health, spread load, and degrade gracefully to\n"
"read-only mode in the event of a failure on the primary host. For help with\n"
"configuring cluster databases, see **[[ %s | %s ]]** in the documentation.\n"
"EOTEXT"
msgstr ""

msgid "Clustering Introduction"
msgstr "Einführung in Clustering"


msgid "Cluster: Search"
msgstr "Cluster: Suche"


#, php-format
msgid ""
"Define one or more fulltext storage services. Here you can configure which\n"
"hosts will handle fulltext search queries and indexing. For help with\n"
"configuring fulltext search clusters, see **[[ %s | %s ]]** in the\n"
"documentation.\n"
"EOTEXT"
msgstr ""

msgid "Address ranges of cluster hosts."
msgstr "Adressbereiche der Cluster-Hosts."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Define a cluster by providing a whitelist of host addresses that are part of "
"the cluster.\n"
"\n"
"Hosts on this whitelist have special powers. These hosts are permitted to "
"bend security rules, and misconfiguring this list can make your install less "
"secure. For more information, see **[[ %s | %s ]]**.\n"
"\n"
"Define a list of CIDR blocks which whitelist all hosts in the cluster and no "
"additional hosts. See the examples below for details.\n"
"\n"
"When cluster addresses are defined, hosts will also reject requests to "
"interfaces which are not whitelisted."
msgstr ""

msgid "Whitelist Specific Addresses"
msgstr "Bestimmte Adressen zulassen"

msgid "Whitelist 1.2.3.*"
msgstr "1.2.3.* zulassen"

msgid "Whitelist 1.2.*.*"
msgstr "1.2.*.* zulassen"

msgid "Allow Any Host (Insecure!)"
msgstr "Jeden Host erlauben (unsicher!)"

msgid "Instance identifier for multi-tenant clusters."
msgstr "Instanzkennung für Multi-Tenant-Cluster."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"WARNING: This is a very advanced option, and only useful for hosting "
"providers running multi-tenant clusters.\n"
"\n"
"If you provide an instance identifier here (normally by injecting it with a "
"`%s`), the server will pass it to subprocesses and commit hooks in the `%s` "
"environmental variable."
msgstr ""

msgid "Activate read-only mode for maintenance or disaster recovery."
msgstr "Nur-Lese-Modus für Wartung oder Notfallwiederherstellung aktivieren."

msgid ""
"WARNING: This is a prototype option and the description below is currently "
"pure fantasy.\n"
"\n"
"Switch the service to read-only mode. In this mode, users will be unable to "
"write new data. Normally, the cluster degrades into this mode automatically "
"when it detects that the database master is unreachable, but you can "
"activate it manually in order to perform maintenance or test configuration."
msgstr ""

msgid "Configure database read replicas."
msgstr "Datenbank-Lesereplikate konfigurieren."

msgid "Configure full-text search services."
msgstr "Volltextsuchdienste konfigurieren."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"This configuration is locked and can not be edited from the web interface. "
"Use %s in %s to edit it."
msgstr ""

msgid "True"
msgstr "True"

msgid "False"
msgstr "False"

msgid "This option does not have a custom type!"
msgstr "Diese Option hat keinen benutzerdefinierten Typ!"

msgid "Configure core options, including URIs."
msgstr "Kernoptionen einschließlich URIs konfigurieren."

msgid "User Guide: Prototype Applications"
msgstr "Benutzerhandbuch: Prototyp-Anwendungen"

msgid ""
"This option allows you to stop this service from sending data to most "
"external\n"
"services: it will disable email, SMS, repository mirroring, remote builds,\n"
"Doorkeeper writes, and webhooks.\n"
"\n"
"This option is intended to allow an instance to be exported, copied, "
"imported,\n"
"and run in a test environment without impacting users. For example, if you "
"are\n"
"migrating to new hardware, you could perform a test migration first with "
"this\n"
"flag set, make sure things work, and then do a production cutover later "
"with\n"
"higher confidence and less disruption.\n"
"\n"
"Without making use of this flag to silence the temporary test environment,\n"
"users would receive duplicate email during the time the test instance and "
"old\n"
"production instance were both in operation.\n"
"EOREMARKUP"
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"PHP date functions will emit a warning if they are called when no default\n"
"server timezone is configured.\n"
"\n"
"Usually, you configure a default timezone in `php.ini` by setting the\n"
"configuration value `date.timezone`.\n"
"\n"
"If you prefer, you can configure a default timezone here instead. To "
"configure\n"
"a default timezone, select a timezone from the\n"
"[[ %s | PHP List of Supported Timezones ]].\n"
"EOREMARKUP"
msgstr ""

msgid "URI where this software is installed."
msgstr "URI, unter der diese Software installiert ist."

msgid ""
"Set the URI where this software is installed. Setting this improves security "
"by preventing cookies from being set on other domains, and allows daemons to "
"send emails with links that have the correct domain."
msgstr ""

msgid "Primary install URI, for multi-environment installs."
msgstr "Primäre Installations-URI für Multi-Umgebungs-Installationen."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"If you have multiple %s environments (like a development/staging environment "
"and a production environment), set the production environment URI here so "
"that emails and other durable URIs will always generate with links pointing "
"at the production environment. If unset, defaults to `%s`. Most installs do "
"not need to set this option."
msgstr ""

msgid "Alternative URIs that can access this service."
msgstr "Alternative URIs, die auf diesen Dienst zugreifen können."

msgid ""
"These alternative URIs will be able to access 'normal' pages on this "
"install. Other features such as OAuth won't work. The major use case for "
"this is moving installs across domains."
msgstr ""

msgid "The timezone this software should use by default."
msgstr "Die Zeitzone, die diese Software standardmäßig verwenden soll."

msgid "US East (EDT)"
msgstr "US-Ost (EDT)"

msgid "US Central (CDT)"
msgstr "US-Mitte (CDT)"

msgid "US Mountain (MDT)"
msgstr "US-Bergzeit (MDT)"

msgid "US West (PDT)"
msgstr "US-West (PDT)"

msgid "Set a string this software should use to prefix cookie names."
msgstr "Eine Zeichenkette festlegen, die diese Software als Präfix für Cookie-Namen verwenden soll."

msgid ""
"Cookies set for x.com are also sent for y.x.com. Assuming instances are "
"running on both domains, this will create a collision preventing you from "
"logging in."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid "Prefix cookie with \"%s\""
msgstr "Cookie mit \\\"%s\\\" prefixen"

msgid "Enable Prototypes"
msgstr "Prototypen aktivieren"

msgid "Disable Prototypes"
msgstr "Prototypen deaktivieren"

msgid "Enable applications which are still under development."
msgstr "Anwendungen aktivieren, die sich noch in der Entwicklung befinden."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"IMPORTANT: The upstream does not provide support for prototype "
"applications.\n"
"\n"
"This platform includes prototype applications which are in an **early stage "
"of development**. By default, prototype applications are disabled, because "
"they are often not yet developed enough to be generally usable. You can "
"enable this option to enable them if you're developing applications or are "
"interested in previewing upcoming features.\n"
"\n"
"To learn more about prototypes, see [[ %s | %s ]].\n"
"\n"
"After enabling prototypes, you can selectively disable them (like normal "
"applications)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Serious business"
msgstr "Ernstes Geschäft"

msgid "Shenanigans"
msgstr "Mumpitz"

msgid "Allows you to remove levity and jokes from the UI."
msgstr "Ermöglicht das Entfernen von Humor und Witzen aus der Benutzeroberfläche."

msgid ""
"By default, this software includes some flavor text in the UI, like a prompt "
"to \"Weigh In\" rather than \"Add Comment\" in Maniphest. If you'd prefer "
"more traditional UI strings like \"Add Comment\", you can set this flag to "
"disable most of the extra flavor."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Text values that match this regex and are also object names will not be "
"linked."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"By default, this software links object names in Remarkup fields to the "
"corresponding object. This regex can be used to modify this behavior; object "
"names that match this regex will not be linked."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid "These paths get appended to your %s environment variable."
msgstr "Diese Pfade werden deiner %s-Umgebungsvariablen angehängt."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"This software sometimes executes other binaries on the server. An example of "
"this is the `%s` command, used to syntax-highlight code written in languages "
"other than PHP. By default, it is assumed that these binaries are in the %s "
"of the user running this software (normally 'apache', 'httpd', or 'nobody'). "
"Here you can add extra directories to the %s environment variable, for when "
"these binaries are in non-standard locations.\n"
"\n"
"Note that you can also put binaries in `%s` (for example, by symlinking "
"them).\n"
"\n"
"The current value of PATH after configuration is applied is:\n"
"\n"
"  lang=text\n"
"  %s"
msgstr ""

msgid "Add One Path"
msgstr "Einen Pfad hinzufügen"

msgid "Add Multiple Paths"
msgstr "Mehrere Pfade hinzufügen"

msgid "Additional configuration options to lock."
msgstr "Zusätzliche zu sperrende Konfigurationsoptionen."

msgid "Additional configuration options to hide."
msgstr "Zusätzliche zu versteckende Konfigurationsoptionen."

msgid "Setup issues to ignore."
msgstr "Zu ignorierende Setup-Probleme."

msgid "Internal."
msgstr "Intern."

msgid "Unit test value."
msgstr "Unit-Test-Wert."

msgid "Applications application"
msgstr "Anwendungen-Anwendung"

#, php-format
msgid "Use the %s to manage enabled applications."
msgstr "%s verwenden, um aktivierte Anwendungen zu verwalten."


msgid "Array containing list of disabled applications."
msgstr "Array mit der Liste deaktivierter Anwendungen."

msgid "Customized settings for applications."
msgstr "Angepasste Einstellungen für Anwendungen."


msgid "Cache namespace."
msgstr "Cache-Namensraum."

msgid "Run Silently"
msgstr "Ohne Ausgaben laufen"

msgid "Run Normally"
msgstr "Normal laufen"

msgid "Stop this software from sending any email, etc."
msgstr "Diese Software daran hindern, E-Mails usw. zu senden."

msgid "Default User-Agent for outgoing HTTP requests made by this software."
msgstr "Standard-User-Agent für ausgehende HTTP-Anfragen dieser Software."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"This User-Agent will be used for most outgoing HTTP requests. When unset, "
"the base URI will be used, with a \" %s/1.0\" suffix."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid "Set default user-agent to \"%s\""
msgstr "Standard-User-Agent auf „%s\" setzen"


#, php-format
msgid ""
"Config option \"%s\" is invalid. The URI must start with \"%s\" or \"%s\"."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Config option \"%s\" is invalid. The URI must contain a dot (\"%s\"), like "
"\"%s\", not just a bare name like \"%s\". Some web browsers will not set "
"cookies on domains with no TLD."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Config option '%s' is invalid. The URI must NOT have a path, e.g. '%s' is "
"OK, but '%s' is not. This software must be '.\n"
"            'installed on an entire domain; it can not be installed on a "
"path."
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Config option \"%s\" is invalid. The timezone identifier must be a valid "
"timezone identifier recognized by PHP, like \"%s\"."
msgstr ""

msgid "Developer / Debugging"
msgstr "Entwickler / Debugging"

msgid "Options for platform developers, including debugging."
msgstr "Optionen für Plattformentwickler, einschließlich Debugging."

msgid "Enable DarkConsole"
msgstr "DarkConsole aktivieren"

msgid "Disable DarkConsole"
msgstr "DarkConsole deaktivieren"

msgid "Enable the debugging console."
msgstr "Die Debugging-Konsole aktivieren."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"DarkConsole is a development and profiling tool built into the web "
"interface. You should leave it disabled unless you are developing or "
"debugging %s.\n"
"\n"
"Once you activate DarkConsole for the install, **you need to enable it for "
"your account before it will actually appear on pages.** You can do this in "
"Settings > Developer Settings.\n"
"\n"
"DarkConsole exposes potentially sensitive data (like queries, stack traces, "
"and configuration) so you generally should not turn it on in production."
msgstr ""

msgid "Always Activate DarkConsole"
msgstr "DarkConsole immer aktivieren"

msgid "Require DarkConsole Activation"
msgstr "DarkConsole-Aktivierung erfordern"

msgid "Activate DarkConsole on every page."
msgstr "DarkConsole auf jeder Seite aktivieren."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"This option allows you to enable DarkConsole on every page, even for logged-"
"out users. This is only really useful if you need to debug something on a "
"logged-out page. You should not enable this option in production.\n"
"\n"
"You must enable DarkConsole by setting '%s' before this option will have any "
"effect."
msgstr ""

msgid "Limit page execution time to debug hangs."
msgstr "Seitenausführungszeit begrenzen, um Hänger zu debuggen."

msgid ""
"This option can help debug pages which are taking a very long time (more "
"than 30 seconds) to render.\n"
"\n"
"If a page is slow to render (but taking less than 30 seconds), the best "
"tools to use to figure out why it is slow are usually the DarkConsole "
"service call profiler and XHProf.\n"
"\n"
"However, if a request takes a very long time to return, some components "
"(like Apache, nginx, or PHP itself) may abort the request before it "
"finishes. This can prevent you from using profiling tools to understand page "
"performance in detail.\n"
"\n"
"In these cases, you can use this option to force the page to abort after a "
"smaller number of seconds (for example, 10), and dump a useful stack trace. "
"This can provide useful information about why a page is hanging.\n"
"\n"
"To use this option, set it to a small number (like 10), and reload a hanging "
"page. The page should exit after 10 seconds and give you a stack trace.\n"
"\n"
"You should turn this option off (set it to 0) when you are done with it. "
"Leaving it on creates a small amount of overhead for all requests, even if "
"they do not hit the time limit."
msgstr ""

msgid "Stop Before HTTP Redirect"
msgstr "Vor HTTP-Weiterleitung anhalten"

msgid "Use Normal HTTP Redirects"
msgstr "Normale HTTP-Weiterleitungen verwenden"

msgid "Confirm before redirecting so DarkConsole can be examined."
msgstr "Vor der Weiterleitung bestätigen, damit DarkConsole untersucht werden kann."

msgid ""
"Normally, this software issues HTTP redirects after a successful POST. This "
"can make it difficult to debug things which happen while processing the "
"POST, because service and profiling information are lost. By setting this "
"configuration option, an interstitial page will be shown instead of "
"automatically redirecting, allowing you to examine service and profiling "
"information. It also makes the UX awful, so you should only enable it when "
"debugging."
msgstr ""

msgid "No profiling"
msgstr "Kein Profiling"

msgid "Profile every request (slow)"
msgstr "Jede Anfrage profilieren (langsam)"

#, php-format
msgid "Profile 0.1%% of all requests"
msgstr "0,1%% aller Anfragen profilieren"

msgid "Automatically profile some percentage of pages."
msgstr "Automatisch einen Prozentsatz der Seiten profilieren."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Normally, pages are profiled only when explicitly requested via DarkConsole. "
"However, it may be useful to profile some pages automatically.\n"
"\n"
"Set this option to a positive integer N to profile 1 / N pages "
"automatically. For example, setting it to 1 will profile every page, while "
"setting it to 1000 will profile 1 page per 1000 requests (i.e., 0.1%% of "
"requests).\n"
"\n"
"Since profiling is slow and generates a lot of data, you should set this to "
"0 in production (to disable it) or to a large number (to collect a few "
"samples, if you're interested in having some data to look at eventually). In "
"development, it may be useful to set it to 1 in order to debug performance "
"problems.\n"
"\n"
"NOTE: You must install XHProf for profiling to work."
msgstr ""

msgid "No performance sampling."
msgstr "Kein Performance-Sampling."

msgid "Sample every request (slow)."
msgstr "Jede Anfrage samplen (langsam)."

#, php-format
msgid "Sample 0.1%% of requests."
msgstr "0,1%% der Anfragen samplen."

msgid "Automatically sample some fraction of requests."
msgstr "Automatisch einen Bruchteil der Anfragen samplen."

msgid ""
"The Multimeter application collects performance samples. You can use this "
"data to help you understand what the software is spending time and resources "
"doing, and to identify problematic access patterns.\n"
"\n"
"This option controls how frequently sampling activates. Set it to some "
"positive integer N to sample every 1 / N pages.\n"
"\n"
"For most installs, the default value (1 sample per 1000 pages) should "
"collect enough data to be useful without requiring much storage or "
"meaningfully impacting performance. If you're investigating performance "
"issues, you can adjust the rate in order to collect more data."
msgstr ""

msgid "Enable developer mode"
msgstr "Entwicklermodus aktivieren"

msgid "Disable developer mode"
msgstr "Entwicklermodus deaktivieren"

msgid "Enable verbose error reporting and disk reads."
msgstr "Ausführliche Fehlerberichterstattung und Festplattenlesezugriffe aktivieren."

msgid ""
"This option enables verbose error reporting (stack traces, error callouts) "
"and forces disk reads of static assets on every reload."
msgstr ""

msgid "Extensions"
msgstr "Erweiterungen"


msgid "Manage extensions."
msgstr "Erweiterungen verwalten."

msgid "Paths to additional phutil libraries to load."
msgstr "Pfade zu zusätzlichen zu ladenden phutil-Bibliotheken."

msgid "Listeners receive callbacks when interesting things occur."
msgstr "Listener erhalten Callbacks, wenn interessante Ereignisse eintreten."

msgid ""
"You can respond to various application events by installing listeners, which "
"will receive callbacks when interesting things occur. Specify a list of "
"classes which extend PhabricatorEventListener here."
msgstr ""

msgid "Mail"
msgstr "Mail"

msgid "Configure Mail."
msgstr "Mail konfigurieren."

msgid ""
"When a user takes an action which generates an email notification (like\n"
"commenting on a Differential revision), the \"From\" address can either be "
"set\n"
"to the user's email address (like \"alincoln@example.com\") or the\n"
"\"metamta.default-address\" address.\n"
"\n"
"The user experience is generally better if the user's real address is used "
"as\n"
"the \"From\" header value, since the messages are easier to organize when "
"they\n"
"appear in mail clients, but this will only work if the server is authorized "
"to\n"
"send email on behalf of the \"From\" domain. Practically, this means:\n"
"\n"
"  - If you are doing an install for Example Corp and all the users will "
"have\n"
"    corporate @corp.example.com addresses and any hosts this software is "
"running\n"
"    on are authorized to send email from corp.example.com, you can enable "
"this\n"
"    to make the user experience a little better.\n"
"  - If you are doing an install for an open source project and your users "
"will\n"
"    be registering via third-party services and/or using personal email\n"
"    addresses, you probably should not enable this or all of your outgoing\n"
"    email might vanish into SFP blackholes.\n"
"  - If your install is anything else, you're safer leaving this off, at "
"least\n"
"    initially, since the risk in turning it on is that your outgoing mail "
"will\n"
"    never arrive.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When a message is sent to multiple recipients (for example, several "
"reviewers on\n"
"a code review), it can either be delieverd as one email to everyone (e.g., "
"\"To:\n"
"alincoln, usgrant, htaft\") or separate emails to each user (e.g., \"To:\n"
"alincoln\", \"To: usgrant\", \"To: htaft\"). The major advantages and "
"disadvantages\n"
"of each approach are:\n"
"\n"
"  - One mail to everyone:\n"
"    - This violates policy controls. The body of the mail is generated "
"without\n"
"      respect for object policies.\n"
"    - Recipients can see To/Cc at a glance.\n"
"    - If you use mailing lists, you won't get duplicate mail if you're\n"
"      a normal recipient and also Cc'd on a mailing list.\n"
"    - Getting threading to work properly is harder, and probably requires\n"
"      making mail less useful by turning off options.\n"
"    - Sometimes people will \"Reply All\", which can send mail to too many\n"
"      recipients. This software will try not to send mail to users who "
"already\n"
"      received a similar message, but can not prevent all stray email "
"arising\n"
"      from \"Reply All\".\n"
"    - Not supported with a private reply-to address.\n"
"    - Mail messages are sent in the server default translation.\n"
"    - Mail that must be delivered over secure channels will leak the "
"recipient\n"
"      list in the \"To\" and \"Cc\" headers.\n"
"  - One mail to each user:\n"
"    - Policy controls work correctly and are enforced per-user.\n"
"    - Recipients need to look in the mail body to see To/Cc.\n"
"    - If you use mailing lists, recipients may sometimes get duplicate\n"
"      mail.\n"
"    - Getting threading to work properly is easier, and threading settings\n"
"      can be customized by each user.\n"
"    - \"Reply All\" will never send extra mail to other users involved in "
"the\n"
"      thread.\n"
"    - Required if private reply-to addresses are configured.\n"
"    - Mail messages are sent in the language of user preference.\n"
"\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can disable the hints under \"REPLY HANDLER ACTIONS\" if users prefer\n"
"smaller messages. The actions themselves will still work properly.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can disable the \"To:\" and \"Cc:\" footers in mail if users prefer "
"smaller\n"
"messages.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can disable the email preference link in emails if users prefer smaller\n"
"emails.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Mail.app on OS X Lion won't respect threading headers unless the subject is\n"
"prefixed with \"Re:\". If you enable this option, this software will add "
"\"Re:\" to\n"
"the subject line of all mail which is expected to thread. If you've set\n"
"'metamta.one-mail-per-recipient', users can override this setting in their\n"
"preferences.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"If true, allow MetaMTA to change mail subjects to put text like '[Accepted]' "
"and\n"
"'[Commented]' in them. This makes subjects more useful, but might break\n"
"threading on some clients. If you've set '%s', users can override this "
"setting\n"
"in their preferences.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"If you enable `%s`, this software uses \"From\" to authenticate users. You "
"can\n"
"additionally enable this setting to try to authenticate with 'Reply-To'. "
"Note\n"
"that this is completely spoofable and insecure (any user can set any 'Reply-"
"To'\n"
"address) but depending on the nature of your install or other "
"deliverability\n"
"conditions this might be okay. Generally, you can't do much more by "
"spoofing\n"
"Reply-To than be annoying (you can write but not read content). But this is\n"
"still **COMPLETELY INSECURE**.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Adapter class to use to transmit mail to the MTA. The default uses\n"
"PHPMailer, which will invoke \"mail\". This is appropriate if mail actually\n"
"works on your host, but if you haven't configured mail it may not be so "
"great.\n"
"A number of other mailers are available (e.g., SES, SendGrid, SMTP, "
"Sendmail,\n"
"custom mailers). This option is deprecated in favor of 'cluster.mailers'.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"By default, this software generates unique reply-to addresses and sends a\n"
"separate email to each recipient when you enable reply handling. This is "
"more\n"
"secure than using \"From\" to establish user identity, but can mean users "
"may\n"
"receive multiple emails when they are on mailing lists. Instead, you can use "
"a\n"
"single, non-unique reply to address and authenticate users based on the "
"\"From\"\n"
"address by setting this to 'true'. This trades away a little bit of "
"security\n"
"for convenience, but it's reasonable in many installs. Object interactions "
"are\n"
"still protected using hashes in the single public email address, so objects\n"
"can not be replied to blindly.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If you want to use a single mailbox for reply mail, you can use this\n"
"and set a common prefix for generated reply addresses. It will\n"
"make use of the fact that a mail-address such as\n"
"`devtools+D123+1hjk213h@example.com` will be delivered to the `devtools`\n"
"user's mailbox. Set this to the left part of the email address and it will "
"be\n"
"prepended to all generated reply addresses.\n"
"\n"
"For example, if you want to use `devtools@example.com`, this should be set\n"
"to `devtools`.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When email is sent, what format should the software use for users' email\n"
"addresses? Valid values are:\n"
"\n"
" - `short`: 'gwashington <gwashington@example.com>'\n"
" - `real`:  'George Washington <gwashington@example.com>'\n"
" - `full`: 'gwashington (George Washington) <gwashington@example.com>'\n"
"\n"
"The default is `full`.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuring Outbound Email"
msgstr "Ausgehende E-Mail konfigurieren"

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Define one or more mail transmission services. For help with configuring\n"
"mailers, see **[[ %s | %s ]]** in the documentation.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Default address used as a \"From\" or \"To\" email address when an address "
"is\n"
"required but no meaningful address is available.\n"
"\n"
"If you configure inbound mail, you generally do not need to set this:\n"
"the software will automatically generate and use a suitable mailbox on the\n"
"inbound mail domain.\n"
"\n"
"Otherwise, this option should be configured to point at a valid mailbox "
"which\n"
"discards all mail sent to it. If you point it at an invalid mailbox, mail "
"sent\n"
"by the software and some mail sent by users will bounce. If you point it at "
"a\n"
"real user mailbox, that user will get a lot of mail they don't want.\n"
"\n"
"For further guidance, see **[[ %s | %s ]]** in the documentation.\n"
"EODOC"
msgstr ""

