msgid "Maximum taskmaster daemon pool size."
msgstr "Maximale Poolgröße des Taskmaster-Dämons."

msgid ""
"Maximum number of taskmaster daemons to run at once. Raising this can "
"increase the maximum throughput of the task queue. The pool will "
"automatically scale down when unutilized.\n"
"\n"
"If you are running a cluster, this limit applies separately to each instance "
"of `phd`. For example, if this limit is set to `4` and you have three hosts "
"running daemons, the effective global limit will be 12.\n"
"\n"
"After changing this value, you must restart the daemons. Most configuration "
"changes are picked up by the daemons automatically, but pool sizes can not "
"be changed without a restart."
msgstr ""

msgid "System user to run daemons as."
msgstr "Systembenutzer, unter dem Dämonen ausgeführt werden sollen."

msgid ""
