msgid "List of Users Without MFA"
msgstr "Liste der Benutzer ohne MFA"

#, php-format
msgid ""
"By default, this software allows users to add multi-factor authentication "
"to\n"
"their accounts, but does not require it. By enabling this option, you can\n"
"force all users to add at least one authentication factor before they can "
"use\n"
"their accounts.\n"
"\n"
"Administrators can query a list of users who do not have MFA configured in\n"
"{nav People}:\n"
"\n"
"  - **[[ %s | %s ]]**\n"
"EOTEXT"
msgstr ""

msgid "Alternate domain to serve files from."
msgstr "Alternative Domain für das Bereitstellen von Dateien."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"By default, this software serves files from the same domain the application "
"is served from. This is convenient, but presents a security risk.\n"
"\n"
"You should configure a CDN or alternate file domain to mitigate this risk. "
"Configuring a CDN will also improve performance. See [[ %s | %s ]] for "
"instructions."
msgstr ""

msgid "Key for HMAC digests."
msgstr "Schlüssel für HMAC-Digests."

msgid ""
"Default key for HMAC digests where the key is not important (i.e., the hash "
"itself is secret). You can change this if you want (to any other string), "
"but doing so will break existing sessions and CSRF tokens. This option is "
"deprecated. Newer code automatically manages HMAC keys."
msgstr ""

msgid "Force users to connect via HTTPS instead of HTTP."
msgstr "Benutzer zur Verbindung über HTTPS statt HTTP zwingen."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"If the web server responds to both HTTP and HTTPS requests but you want "
"users to connect with only HTTPS, you can set this to `true` to make this "
"service redirect HTTP requests to HTTPS.\n"
"\n"
"Normally, you should just configure your server not to accept HTTP traffic, "
"but this setting may be useful if you originally used HTTP and have now "
"switched to HTTPS but don't want to break old links, or if your webserver "
"sits behind a load balancer which terminates HTTPS connections and you can "
"not reasonably configure more granular behavior there.\n"
"\n"
"IMPORTANT: A request is identified as HTTP or HTTPS by examining the PHP "
"`%s` variable. If you run Apache/mod_php this will probably be set correctly "
"for you automatically, but if you run as CGI/FCGI (e.g., through nginx or "
"lighttpd), you need to configure your web server so that it passes the value "
"correctly based on the connection type.\n"
"\n"
"If you configure clustering, note that this setting is ignored by "
"intracluster requests."
msgstr ""

msgid "Force HTTPS"
msgstr "HTTPS erzwingen"

msgid "Allow HTTP"
msgstr "HTTP zulassen"

msgid "Require all users to configure multi-factor authentication."
msgstr "Alle Benutzer zur Einrichtung von Multi-Faktor-Authentifizierung verpflichten."

msgid "Multi-Factor Required"
msgstr "Multi-Faktor erforderlich"

msgid "Multi-Factor Optional"
msgstr "Multi-Faktor optional"

msgid "Determines which URI protocols are valid for links and redirects."
msgstr "Bestimmt, welche URI-Protokolle für Links und Weiterleitungen gültig sind."

msgid ""
"When users write comments which have URIs, they will be automatically turned "
"into clickable links if the URI protocol appears in this set.\n"
"\n"
"This set of allowed protocols is primarily intended to prevent security "
"issues with \"javascript:\" and other potentially dangerous URI handlers.\n"
"\n"
"This set is also used to enforce valid redirect URIs. This service will "
"refuse to issue a HTTP \"Location\" redirect to a URI with a protocol not on "
"this set.\n"
"\n"
"Usually, \"http\" and \"https\" should be present in this set. If you remove "
"one or both protocols, some features which rely on links or redirects may "
"not work."
msgstr ""

msgid "Whitelists editor protocols for \"Open in Editor\"."
msgstr "Editor-Protokolle für \\\"Im Editor öffnen\\\" zulassen."

msgid ""
"Users can configure a URI pattern to open files in a text editor. The URI "
"must use a protocol on this whitelist."
msgstr ""

msgid "Embed YouTube videos"
msgstr "YouTube-Videos einbinden"

msgid "Don't embed YouTube videos"
msgstr "Keine YouTube Videos einbinden"

msgid "Determines whether or not YouTube videos get embedded."
msgstr "Bestimmt, ob YouTube-Videos eingebettet werden."

msgid ""
"If you enable this, linked YouTube videos will be embedded inline. This has "
"mild security implications (you'll leak referrers to YouTube) and is pretty "
"silly (but sort of awesome)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Blacklist subnets to prevent user-initiated outbound requests."
msgstr "Subnetze sperren, um benutzerinitiierte ausgehende Anfragen zu verhindern."

msgid ""
"Users can make requests to other services from service hosts in some "
"circumstances (for example, by creating a repository with a remote URL).\n"
"\n"
"This may represent a security vulnerability if services on the same subnet "
"will accept commands or reveal private information over unauthenticated HTTP "
"GET, based on the source IP address. In particular, all hosts in EC2 have "
"access to such a service.\n"
"\n"
"This option defines a list of netblocks which requests will never be issued "
"to. Generally, you should list all private IP space here."
msgstr ""

msgid "No Outbound Requests"
msgstr "Keine ausgehenden Anfragen"

msgid "Use HSTS"
msgstr "HSTS verwenden"

msgid "Do Not Use HSTS"
msgstr "HSTS nicht verwenden"

msgid "Enable HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS)."
msgstr "HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) aktivieren."

msgid ""
"HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) sends a header which instructs "
"browsers that the site should only be accessed over HTTPS, never HTTP. This "
"defuses an attack where an adversary gains access to your network, then "
"proxies requests through an unsecured link.\n"
"\n"
"Do not enable this option if you serve (or plan to ever serve) unsecured "
"content over plain HTTP. It is very difficult to undo this change once "
"users' browsers have accepted the setting."
msgstr ""

msgid "Configure master encryption keys."
msgstr "Master-Verschlüsselungsschlüssel konfigurieren."


#, php-format
msgid "Config option '%s' is invalid. The URI must start with '%s' or '%s'."
msgstr "Konfigurationsoption '%s' ist ungültig. Die URI muss mit '%s' oder '%s' beginnen."

#, php-format
msgid ""
"Config option '%s' is invalid. The URI must contain a dot ('.'), like '%s', "
"not just a bare name like '%s'. Some web browsers will not set cookies on "
"domains with no TLD."
msgstr ""

