#, php-format
msgid ""
"Harbormaster build objects work somewhat differently from objects in many "
"other\n"
"applications. Most application objects can be edited directly using "
"synchronous\n"
"APIs (like `maniphest.edit`, `differential.revision.edit`, and so on).\n"
"\n"
"However, builds require long-running background processing and Habormaster\n"
"objects have a more complex lifecycle than most other application objects "
"and\n"
"may spend significant periods of time locked by daemon processes during "
"build\n"
"execution. A synchronous edit might need to wait an arbitrarily long amount "
"of\n"
"time for this lock to become available so the edit could be applied.\n"
"\n"
"Additionally, some edits may also require an arbitrarily long amount of time "
"to\n"
"//complete//. For example, aborting a build may execute cleanup steps which\n"
"take minutes (or even hours) to complete.\n"
"\n"
"Since a synchronous API could not guarantee it could return results to the\n"
"caller in a reasonable amount of time, the edit API for Harbormaster build\n"
"objects is asynchronous: to update a Harbormaster build or build target, "
"use\n"
"this API (`harbormaster.sendmessage`) to send it a message describing an "
"edit\n"
"you would like to effect or additional information you want to provide.\n"
"The message will be processed by the daemons once the build or target "
"reaches\n"
"a suitable state to receive messages.\n"
"\n"
"Select an object to send a message to using the `receiver` parameter. This\n"
"API method can send messages to multiple types of objects:\n"
"\n"
"<table>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <th>Object Type</th>\n"
"    <th>PHID Example</th>\n"
"    <th>Description</th>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Buildable</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBB-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Build</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBD-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Build Target</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBT-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"</table>\n"
"\n"
"See below for specifics on sending messages to different object types.\n"
"EOREMARKUP"
msgstr ""
"Harbormaster-Build-Objekte funktionieren etwas anders als Objekte in vielen "
"anderen Anwendungen. Die meisten Anwendungsobjekte können direkt über "
"synchrone APIs bearbeitet werden. Builds hingegen erfordern langwierige "
"Hintergrundverarbeitung und Harbormaster-Objekte haben einen komplexeren "
"Lebenszyklus. Für eine Bearbeitung wird diese API "
"(`harbormaster.sendmessage`) verwendet, um eine Nachricht mit der "
"gewünschten Bearbeitung oder zusätzlichen Informationen zu senden. Die "
"Nachricht wird von den Daemons verarbeitet, sobald der Build oder das Ziel "
"einen geeigneten Zustand erreicht, um Nachrichten zu empfangen.\n"
"\n"
"Ein Objekt zum Senden einer Nachricht mit dem `receiver`-Parameter "
"auswählen. Diese API-Methode kann Nachrichten an mehrere Objekttypen "
"senden:\n"
"\n"
"<table>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <th>Objekttyp</th>\n"
"    <th>PHID-Beispiel</th>\n"
"    <th>Beschreibung</th>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Buildable</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBB-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Build</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBD-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"  <tr>\n"
"    <td>Harbormaster Build Target</td>\n"
"    <td>`PHID-HMBT-...`</td>\n"
"    <td>%s</td>\n"
"  </tr>\n"
"</table>\n"
"\n"
"Siehe unten für Details zum Senden von Nachrichten an verschiedene "
"Objekttypen.\n"
"EOREMARKUP"

msgid "Updating Builds"
msgstr "Builds aktualisieren"

msgid ""
"You can use this method (`harbormaster.sendmessage`) to send control "
"commands\n"
"to Buildables and Builds.\n"
"\n"
"Specify the Build or Buildable to receive the control command by providing "
"its\n"
"PHID in the `receiver` parameter.\n"
"\n"
"Sending a control command to a Buildable has the same effect as sending it "
"to\n"
"each Build for the Buildable. For example, sending a \"Pause\" message to a\n"
"Buildable will pause all builds for the Buildable (or at least attempt to).\n"
"\n"
"When sending control commands, the `unit` and `lint` parameters of this API\n"
"method must be omitted. You can not report lint or unit results directly to\n"
"a Build or Buildable, and can not report them alongside a control command.\n"
"\n"
"More broadly, you can not report build results directly to a Build or\n"
"Buildable. Instead, report results to a Build Target.\n"
"\n"
"See below for a list of control commands.\n"
"\n"
"EOREMARKUP"
msgstr "Diese Methode (`harbormaster.sendmessage`) verwenden, um Steuerbefehle an Build-Kandidaten und Builds zu senden.\n\nDen Build oder den Build-Kandidaten, der den Steuerbefehl empfangen soll, durch Angabe seiner PHID im `receiver`-Parameter angeben.\n\nDas Senden eines Steuerbefehls an einen Build-Kandidaten hat denselben Effekt wie das Senden an jeden Build dieses Build-Kandidaten.\n\nBeim Senden von Steuerbefehlen müssen die `unit`- und `lint`-Parameter dieser API-Methode weggelassen werden. Build-Ergebnisse können nicht direkt an einen Build oder einen Build-Kandidaten gemeldet werden. Stattdessen Ergebnisse an ein Build-Ziel melden.\n\nSiehe unten für eine Liste der Steuerbefehle.\n\nEOREMARKUP"

msgid "Message Type"
msgstr "Nachrichtentyp"

msgid "Control Commands"
msgstr "Steuerbefehle"

