msgid "Send Stamps"
msgstr "Stempel senden"

msgid ""
"Outgoing mail is stamped with labels like `actor(alice)` which can be used "
"to\n"
"write client mail rules to organize mail. By default, these stamps are sent\n"
"in an `X-Phabricator-Stamps` header.\n"
"\n"
"If you use a client which can not use headers to route mail (like Gmail),\n"
"you can also include the stamps in the message body so mail rules based on\n"
"body content can route messages.\n"
"EOREMARKUP"
msgstr ""

msgid "Mail Headers"
msgstr "Mail-Header"

